    <h1>Data and Analysis Project (UN-OCHA)</h1>

    <p>Welcome to an early pilot of UN-OCHA's <cite>Data and Analysis Project</cite>.  The goal of this project is to make curated (reliable, comparable, and sourced) data available to the humanitarian community to help with preparedness and operations during emergencies.</p>

    <p><b>Note:</b> this site is solely for preview purposes; use any data you find here with caution.</p>

    <dl>

      <dt><a href="/countries/">Countries</a></dt>
      <dd>Start here to view humanitarian indicators by country.  You can see a list of all available indicators for that country, and drill down for more information.</dd>

      <dt><a href="/indicators/">Indicators</a></dt>
      <dd>Start here to view a list of all available humanitarian indicators for all countries.  You can drill down in each indicator for more information.</dd>

      <dt><a href="/datasets/">Source datasets</a></dt>
      <dd>Start here to view a list of the source datasets for the indicators on this site.  You can drill down in each dataset to specific indicators from that source. </dd>

